parameters:
Luuna: I was the one who taught you "not to hold grudges against
people," yet...

Luuna: Back then, I was blinded by hatred for Hilda, and as a result,
I fell into their trap.

Cain: Heh heh, that Hilda guy, I heard he's got a face like a ghost
from the wound Luuna gave him. It's more humiliating than death.
Serves him right.
Becky: Enough with the unnecessary comments.
Becky: Hey, Luuna, what are you going to do now?
Luuna: No more... I won't fight anymore.

Luuna: This battle made it clear. I simply can't win against Lucia,
Sylvia, or Zena. For a while...

Becky: That flower was probably left by the person who sent the
letter.

Becky: It's strange. That flower doesn't wilt at all. In fact, it's
thriving.

Luuna: A flower that doesn't wilt... There must be a meaning behind
this flower being placed here.
Becky: Eh... The meaning of a flower that doesn't wilt?

Luuna: I see... The path I should take from now on... is what this
flower's language signifies.

Luuna: This flower is 'Rose Not Wither.' Its language means an
unwilting flower... a flower that doesn't give up...
Luuna: The sender of that letter is telling me this.

Luuna: "Do not wither! Do not falter! Do not give up!"... that's what
they're saying.
Luuna: I am... an unwilting flower.

Luuna: I... will set out on a journey to find Regnus Grahardt once
more. Becky...
Becky: I know! I'll help too!
Luuna: Let's go to the imperial capital, Jupiterino.

Cain: Hey! You guys completely forgot about repaying the debt to the
village!
Becky: Oh my, was there such a debt? Right, Luuna?
Luuna: Hehe... Well now. So, Cain, are you coming with us?
Cain: Geez...! No way, I don't want to go through scary stuff again.

Noah: So Noah, take care of my lower half~. My legs are still in bad
shape~.
